title: Scentre sells four shopping centres
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › Scentre sells four shopping centres Scentre sells four shopping centres Next Story Prev Story 36 min ago Read more: The Age 
The operator of the Westfield brand in Australia, Scentre Group has sold four shopping centres in NSW and Queensland for more than $780 million. Scentre has agreed to sell its Figtree, Strathpine, Warrawong centres to affiliates of Blackstone Real Estate Asia and its North Rocks centre to Challenger for a combined total of $783 million.
